# Playwright And TypeScript Quality Rules

## TypeScript

- Keep strict TypeScript compatibility.
- Avoid `any`; if unavoidable, keep it local and explain why.
- Prefer explicit domain types for shared data and suite metadata.
- Do not silence errors with broad casts or blanket `// eslint-disable` comments.

## Playwright Tests

- Prefer semantic locators: `getByRole`, `getByLabel`, `getByText`, and `getByTestId` where appropriate.
- Prefer web-first assertions such as `await expect(locator).toBeVisible()`.
- Avoid arbitrary sleeps and hard waits.
- Avoid custom retry loops around UI interactions; use Playwright waiting and assertions.
- Keep test titles descriptive and stable.
- Keep tests business-readable; move repeated mechanics into pages, fixtures, or helpers.

## Setup And Auth

- Keep reusable setup in `setup.ts` or fixtures.
- Do not hardcode credentials.
- Keep committed `.env` values dummy-only.
- Use environment variables or CI secrets for real authentication.

## Templates

- Keep template files under `templates/` with `.template.*` names.
- Do not make templates executable or compiled by default.
- Update templates when framework conventions change.
